<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - TORQUE RODS - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the new or rebushed torque rod in the bottom cap and install washers and locknuts.
                Do not torque nuts at this time.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position torque rod on forward face of frame hanger legs and assemble bolts, washers,
                locknuts and any alignment shims. Tighten locknuts to 150-205 ft-lbs. (203-278 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk document="s03007_10.xml" xrefid="f0300713">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten locknuts at axle end of torque rod (
                <hotlnk document="s03007_10.xml" xrefid="f0300713">Figure 13</hotlnk>) to the same torque as in step 2
                above.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten rebound bolt locknuts to 49-66 ft-lbs. (66-89 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk document="s03007_10.xml" xrefid="f0300713">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
